issue.title: Notifiy user of invalid trace rate setting
issue.body:
Performance tracing doesn't work if both the tracesSampler and the traceSampler rate is set. There should be some sort of error when the user does it.

This enlightenment come out of a recent discussion on Discord.

comment.body:
We check if this class is available on app start [here](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-java/blob/93a76ca3ed5e22b37a521784f4b601668bfa7e07/sentry-android-core/src/main/java/io/sentry/android/core/AndroidOptionsInitializer.java#L146-L147), which itself [prints an error log here](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-java/blob/93a76ca3ed5e22b37a521784f4b601668bfa7e07/sentry-android-core/src/main/java/io/sentry/android/core/LoadClass.java#L24C19-L24C19).

So this is definitely not a crash, but maybe we simply shouldn't log this as an error.

issue.title: Symbol upload for Flutter framework
issue.body:
> After [some testing](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-dart/tree/vaind/profiling-experiments?rgh-link-date=2023-07-20T19%3A12%3A23Z), It seems like the native profiler could be the way to go, at least for iOS and macOS. However, I'm having issues with the symbolication - all the flutter symbols (e.g. referencing `/private/var/containers/Bundle/Application/2D6824B6-DC93-4F60-AFC2-ADE201585EC6/Runner.app/Frameworks/Flutter.framework/Flutter`) in [this profile](https://sentry-sdks.sentry.io/profiling/profile/sentry-flutter/0d47001e91a949668c4a84cccdf4fa3d/flamechart/?colorCoding=by+system+vs+application+frame&fov=0%2C0%2C933058048%2C32&query=&sorting=call+order&tid=85775&view=top+down) are unresolved (symbol not found). I don't know - was there some custom handling in the symbolicator for flutter-specific symbols? Maybe that doesn't get triggered when the transaction comes from swift... Also I've tested [triggering an error](https://sentry-sdks.sentry.io/issues/4339846487/events/877f3d88ae5d41aabeeece7e4cb6223f/?project=5428562) in swift and the image seems resolved but the frames say `redacted`. Do you know what that is about @marandaneto ?

OK so at least in errors, the issue of some stack frames not being symbolicated is due to dSYMs missing for the Flutter.framework (or FlutterMacOS.framework). They're currently not shipped with Flutter at the moment so the dart plugin won't upload them to Sentry and thus they can't be used for symbolication, see https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/117404#issuecomment-1360064880

_Originally posted by @vaind in https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-dart/issues/1106#issuecomment-1650547779_

## Possible solutions:

* upload in the dart plugin
* use craft, although this is normally used to upload during an SDK release: https://github.com/getsentry/craft#symbol-collector-symbol-collector
* introduce a flutter-specific symbol server - https://github.com/getsentry/team-processing/issues/83

pull_request.title: feat: profiling for iOS/macOS
pull_request.body:
## :scroll: Description

This brings initial support for profiling on iOS and macOS, via native Sentry cocoa SDK profiler.

I've tried extracting a couple of preparation PRs but there's still some refactoring going on here, hope that doesn't make reviewing too hard. Namely, `SentryNative` now acts as an adapter to implementations of `SentryNativeBinding`. The original `SentryNativeChannel` is one implementation, `SentryNativeCocoa` is another one. Also, error handling has moved from `SentryNativeChannel` to `SentryNative` so that it can be shared by all binding implementations.

## :bulb: Motivation and Context

#1106 

## :green_heart: How did you test it?


## :pencil: Checklist
<!--- Put an `x` in the boxes that apply -->
- [x] I reviewed submitted code
- [x] I added tests to verify changes
- [x] No new PII added or SDK only sends newly added PII if `sendDefaultPii` is enabled
- [x] I updated the docs if needed - https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-docs/pull/7880
- [x] All tests passing
- [x] No breaking changes


## TODO in this PR

* [x] integration test (because we can't unit test FFI)
* [x] [fix generated FFI bindings](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-dart/pull/1648) - currently crashes with the latest binding generated by the pinned ffigen version. I've temporarily replaced the binding in this PR to an older version that worked. The issue seems to be with creating an NSObject where an int should be returned from startProfilerForTrace()


## :crystal_ball: Next steps

* [x] add changelog
* [ ] #1613 
* [ ] [better symbolication](https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-dart/issues/1106#issuecomment-1717430776)
